    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A spontaneous phenomenon where a thin film on a surface ruptures into an ensemble of separated objects, like droplets, stripes, or pillars. This occurs when a liquid film retracts from a solid to form a bead-shaped drop.</Note_Text>
